Eskom is the biggest risk to Anglo American’s South African business in the short term, says CEO Mark Cutifani. Anglo remains one of SA’s leading mining companies with domestic assets in platinum group metals, diamonds, coal, iron ore and manganese despite selling all its coal mines that supply Eskom. If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link  to go to the full article:  Anglo CEO: Eskom our biggest threat If you would like to subscribe to BusinessLIVE to read the full story, please click here.